    "description": "The Harmony Trajectory Subsetter is a Harmony backend service developed as part of the NASA Earth Observing System Data and Information System (EOSDIS). The service can subset trajectory data, structured as 1-dimensional along-track arrays, while preserving aggregated segments where applicable. Supports variable, temporal and spatial subsetting by bounding box or polygon shape files (GeoJSON). Supported data include ICESat-2, SMAP L2 and GEDI waveform data.",
